This paper deals with the evaluation of password complexity and strength, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses human biases and the techniques used by attackers to recover stolen credentials, which are related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper addresses the challenges of implementing password policies in practice, which is related to cybercrime (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
